    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Small paintings, generally smaller than two feet in any dimension, originally intended to be hung in small rooms or "gabinetti" of collectors. Typically dating to the 16th century and later; the support may be panel, ivory, metal, or canvas. The subjects depicted are of small scale, intended for viewing at close range.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000026701/Mayer, Dictionary of Art Terms and Techniques (1969)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079228/Grove Art Online (2008-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Pequeñas pinturas de caballete de finales del siglo XVII al XIX, con el propósito de ser colgadas en pequeños cuartos y ser vistos de manera cercana.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Relatief kleine schilderijen uit de late 17e eeuw tot de 19e eeuw, bedoeld om opgehangen te worden in kamers en om van dichtbij te worden bekeken.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Kleines Staffeleibild des späten 17. bis 19. Jahrhunderts, zum Aufhängen in kleinen Räumen und zum Betrachten aus der Nahdistanz gedacht.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Pinturas pequenas, geralmente menores do que 60 centímetros em qualquer dimensão, feitas originalmente para serem penduradas em pequenas salas ou em "gabinetti" de colecionadores. Normalmente, datadas do século XVI ou depois; o suporte pode ser painel, marfim, metal ou tela. Os temas representados são de pequena escala, feitos para serem vistos de perto.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
